cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes a novel recurrent neural network (RNN) based algorithm for precipitation nowcasting, which is a problem related to weather forecasting. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most general sub-category for machine learning-related papers. The paper also uses radar data, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel information bridge and a multi-sigmoid loss function, which are related to network architecture and optimization, respectively, indicating that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with time-series data, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.SD (Sound).
